{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430/comments/117086677.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo:6224c0d5a592..02e1fde5e923?path=src%2Fgui%2Fplugins%2Fscene3d%2FGzScene3D.qml"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430/_/diff#comment-117086677"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 430, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430"}}, "title": "Add Follow mode to GUI"}, "content": {"raw": "Once we have a [snackbar](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gui/issues/44/notification-snackbar) on ign-gui, this message could go there as a persistent notification that needs to be dismissed by the user.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Once we have a <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gui/issues/44/notification-snackbar\" rel=\"nofollow\">snackbar</a> on ign-gui, this message could go there as a persistent notification that needs to be dismissed by the user.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-16T20:26:15.300770+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "inline": {"to": 24, "from": null, "path": "src/gui/plugins/scene3d/GzScene3D.qml"}, "updated_on": "2019-09-16T20:26:15.312408+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 117086677}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430/comments/117102098.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo:1a828ef91205..02e1fde5e923?path=src%2Fgui%2Fplugins%2Fscene3d%2FGzScene3D.qml"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430/_/diff#comment-117102098"}}, "parent": {"id": 117086677, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430/comments/117086677.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430/_/diff#comment-117086677"}}, "depth": 1}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 430, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430"}}, "title": "Add Follow mode to GUI"}, "content": {"raw": "added a `todo` note to replace the text msg with a snackbar when it\u2019s available. [1a828ef](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/commits/1a828ef91205b65b17d5fa297e41882e83cd65b4)", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>added a <code>todo</code> note to replace the text msg with a snackbar when it\u2019s available. <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/commits/1a828ef91205b65b17d5fa297e41882e83cd65b4\" rel=\"nofollow\">1a828ef</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-16T23:42:05.739041+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Ian Chen", "uuid": "{eaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:10b01d41-a2e9-4a41-a907-e6e2f03b6cd5/1e4adcdf-1946-4280-9aea-eb5f15a7f912/128"}}, "nickname": "Ian Chen", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:10b01d41-a2e9-4a41-a907-e6e2f03b6cd5"}, "inline": {"to": 24, "from": null, "path": "src/gui/plugins/scene3d/GzScene3D.qml"}, "updated_on": "2019-09-16T23:42:05.749541+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 117102098}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430/comments/117089956.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430/_/diff#comment-117089956"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 430, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430"}}, "title": "Add Follow mode to GUI"}, "content": {"raw": "I like it how the follow offset is adjusted as the user orbits the scene, really intuitive! Just a few comments below:\n\n* While following a model, clicking `Move To` for another model makes the camera jump to the new model and then back to the old one. Can we disable `Move To` while `Follow` is running?\n\n* I think the current parameters work well for mobile robots, but they can be a bit dizzying when used with objects that are rapidly changing their orientation, such as below. Setting the P gain to zero makes that situation much better. Do you think you could expose the P gain through the plugin's SDF? I think this could be handy for tracking non-robot objects.\n\n    P gain == 0.01\n\n    ![dizzy_box.gif](data/bitbucket.org/repo/8zodKzn/images/295606903-dizzy_box.gif)\n\n    P gain == 0\n\n    ![zero_gain_box.gif](data/bitbucket.org/repo/8zodKzn/images/1911577059-zero_gain_box.gif)\n\n* Do you think it would be much more work to support choosing a visual to be tracked at startup through SDF? I think the logic should support the model being spawned at any time.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I like it how the follow offset is adjusted as the user orbits the scene, really intuitive! Just a few comments below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>While following a model, clicking <code>Move To</code> for another model makes the camera jump to the new model and then back to the old one. Can we disable <code>Move To</code> while <code>Follow</code> is running?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>I think the current parameters work well for mobile robots, but they can be a bit dizzying when used with objects that are rapidly changing their orientation, such as below. Setting the P gain to zero makes that situation much better. Do you think you could expose the P gain through the plugin's SDF? I think this could be handy for tracking non-robot objects.</p>\n<p>P gain == 0.01</p>\n<p><img alt=\"dizzy_box.gif\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/8zodKzn/images/295606903-dizzy_box.gif\" /></p>\n<p>P gain == 0</p>\n<p><img alt=\"zero_gain_box.gif\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/8zodKzn/images/1911577059-zero_gain_box.gif\" /></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Do you think it would be much more work to support choosing a visual to be tracked at startup through SDF? I think the logic should support the model being spawned at any time.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-16T20:56:33.913603+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": "2019-09-16T20:56:33.922314+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 117089956}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430/comments/117102487.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430/_/diff#comment-117102487"}}, "parent": {"id": 117089956, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430/comments/117089956.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430/_/diff#comment-117089956"}}, "depth": 1}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 430, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430"}}, "title": "Add Follow mode to GUI"}, "content": {"raw": "Added params for setting follow target and p gain. [1a828ef](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/commits/1a828ef91205b65b17d5fa297e41882e83cd65b4)\n\nDisabling the `Move To` menu when `Follow`  mode is enabled seems to be more difficult than expected. The entity context menu needs to know the current state of the user camera but it currently doesn\u2019t because it\u2019s an standalone module. I have to rethink about  how the context menu should be implemented. It may have to be an integral part of the Scene3d plugin. For now, I fixed the camera jumping issue when `Move To` is requested.  [1a828ef](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/commits/1a828ef91205b65b17d5fa297e41882e83cd65b4)", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Added params for setting follow target and p gain. <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/commits/1a828ef91205b65b17d5fa297e41882e83cd65b4\" rel=\"nofollow\">1a828ef</a></p>\n<p>Disabling the <code>Move To</code> menu when <code>Follow</code>  mode is enabled seems to be more difficult than expected. The entity context menu needs to know the current state of the user camera but it currently doesn\u2019t because it\u2019s an standalone module. I have to rethink about  how the context menu should be implemented. It may have to be an integral part of the Scene3d plugin. For now, I fixed the camera jumping issue when <code>Move To</code> is requested.  <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/commits/1a828ef91205b65b17d5fa297e41882e83cd65b4\" rel=\"nofollow\">1a828ef</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-16T23:48:56.583882+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Ian Chen", "uuid": "{eaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:10b01d41-a2e9-4a41-a907-e6e2f03b6cd5/1e4adcdf-1946-4280-9aea-eb5f15a7f912/128"}}, "nickname": "Ian Chen", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:10b01d41-a2e9-4a41-a907-e6e2f03b6cd5"}, "updated_on": "2019-09-16T23:48:56.600287+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 117102487}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430/comments/117102773.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430/_/diff#comment-117102773"}}, "parent": {"id": 117102487, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430/comments/117102487.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430/_/diff#comment-117102487"}}, "depth": 2}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 430, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430"}}, "title": "Add Follow mode to GUI"}, "content": {"raw": "Here\u2019s an example of configuring the camera follow params:\n\n```\n        <camera_follow>\n          <p_gain>0</p_gain>\n          <target>box</target>\n        </camera_follow>\n```\n\n\u200c", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Here\u2019s an example of configuring the camera follow params:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>        <span class=\"nt\">&lt;camera_follow&gt;</span>\n          <span class=\"nt\">&lt;p_gain&gt;</span>0<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/p_gain&gt;</span>\n          <span class=\"nt\">&lt;target&gt;</span>box<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/target&gt;</span>\n        <span class=\"nt\">&lt;/camera_follow&gt;</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>\u200c</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-16T23:53:48.727862+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Ian Chen", "uuid": "{eaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:10b01d41-a2e9-4a41-a907-e6e2f03b6cd5/1e4adcdf-1946-4280-9aea-eb5f15a7f912/128"}}, "nickname": "Ian Chen", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:10b01d41-a2e9-4a41-a907-e6e2f03b6cd5"}, "updated_on": "2019-09-16T23:53:54.415186+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 117102773}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430/comments/117103856.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430/_/diff#comment-117103856"}}, "parent": {"id": 117102773, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430/comments/117102773.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430/_/diff#comment-117102773"}}, "depth": 3}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 430, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/430.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/430"}}, "title": "Add Follow mode to GUI"}, "content": {"raw": "Thanks! LGTM, I added this to the example world: f3df3f5\n\nApproving, let's merge when CI comes back happy.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Thanks! LGTM, I added this to the example world: <a href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/commits/f3df3f5\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">f3df3f5</a></p>\n<p>Approving, let's merge when CI comes back happy.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-17T00:13:58.550682+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": "2019-09-17T00:13:58.559773+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 117103856}], "page": 1, "size": 6}